  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Break your <strong>meat-free sausages</strong> into rough pieces</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick, matching lid) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1620663073780-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1620663073780-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1620663073780-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1620663073780-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1620663073780-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>meat-free sausage pieces </strong>with your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1620663077619-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1620663077619-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1620663077619-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1620663077619-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1620663077619-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the meat-free sausage meat is cooking, add your <strong>wholewheat spaghetti</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-12 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>spaghetti</strong> and return to the pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1620663085390-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1620663085390-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1620663085390-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1620663085390-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1620663085390-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, reboil a full kettle</p><p>Roughly chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> halved cherry tomatoes</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min further or until the tomatoes have begun to break down</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1620663090471-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1620663090471-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1620663090471-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1620663090471-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1620663090471-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve<strong> </strong>your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 150ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>spinach </strong>to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it until wilted</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water </strong>until it's cool enough to handle, then squeeze out any excess water<strong> </strong>(clean hands is best!)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1620663096487-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1620663096487-x400.jpg",
